cond largest type. The flatcar comes with a removable trailer, and all the cars have die-cast metal tires to connect easily to the track.","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/57213-lionel-the-scout1.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/5jTWiFQNZwtDxuaThk7bd3.jpg","credit":"","align":"","id":"5jTWiFQNZwtDxuaThk7bd3","mos":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/5jTWiFQNZwtDxuaThk7bd3.jpg","alt":""},"id":"f7ad70e3-f0b9-4321-bdbd-a7ee42455b39","type":"image"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["We took a detailed look at every train car for paint smudges, paint chips and any other issues. On the train we purchased, one of the conductors located in the back of the locomotive has a noticeable blue paint smudge on the back of his head. Also, the orange stripe that runs from back to front on each side of the train has a tiny black smudge near the cabin numbers. It is very small, but we were extremely meticulous in our train detailing.","The rest of the train cars, including the additional yellow car that is hauled by the flat car, look excellent. All of the paint is finely detailed; even the smallest of print looks great."]},"id":"67afaf41-4544-46fb-ad61-a970c2ecb9c6","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Train Details"},"id":"fd35855b-6326-4686-8e82-f4f86a0f755f","type":"heading"},{"data":{"path":"/bBek55H9SHVcuoWsAAy7Pj.jpg","link":{"href":"","rel":null,"target":""},"caption":"The locomotive is as strong as it is good looking. We added extra weights to the train cars to simulate the addition of other train cars. We maxed the test out at 13 additional pounds, and the Scout had no problem pulling the additional weight. If you ever feel like expanding your train set, your locomotive should have no problem hauling around additional cars.","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/57213-lionel-the-scout3.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/bBek55H9SHVcuoWsAAy7Pj.jpg","credit":"","align":"","id":"bBek55H9S